issues.description: The template’s Lecture constructor stub only declares three parameters (lectureName, numberOfInscribedStudents, numberOfGuestStudents), but the problem spec and solution require a five-parameter constructor initializing all attributes in the order shown in the UML (lectureName, numberOfInscribedStudents, numberOfGuestStudents, numberOfLecturers, numberOfTutors). This mismatch will confuse students and cause the tests for a five-argument constructor to fail.
issues.suggested_fix: Update the constructor signature in Lecture.java (template) to include all five parameters in the correct order: String lectureName, int numberOfInscribedStudents, int numberOfGuestStudents, int numberOfLecturers, int numberOfTutors, and implement assignments for the last two fields accordingly.
